de.mpa.io

Class MascotGenericFile

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.mpa.io.MascotGenericFile
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.compomics.util.interfaces.SpectrumFile, Serializable, Comparable

    public class MascotGenericFile
extends Object
implements com.compomics.util.interfaces.SpectrumFile, Serializable
    This class maps a Mascot Generic File to memory. It allows for search and retrieval as well as comparing functionality.
    Author:
    Thilo Muth
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

      • compareTo

        public int compareTo(Object anObject)
        This method compares two MascotGenericFiles and allows them to be sorted relative to each other. Sorting is done on the basis of precursor M/Z (we cannot always calculate mass due to the possible absence of charge information).
        Specified by:
        compareTo in interface Comparable
        Parameters:
        anObject - MascotGenericFile to compare this instance to.
        Returns:
        int with the code for sorting (negative, positive or 0).
